  "@type": "ActorManifest",
  "id": "did:web:ooyake.etzhayyim.com",
  "name": "ooyake",
  "displayName": "公 — World Government Atlas (civic wayfinding map)",
  "displayNameJa": "公",
  "displayNameEn": "Ooyake",
  "description": "kotoba-Datomic-native STRUCTURAL atlas of every government unit on Earth — supranational → country → region/subdivision → prefecture → municipality/ward → ministry (省) → agency (庁) → bureau (局) → division (課) → section → 窓口 (madoguchi) — each carrying 住所 (address) / 窓口 (service window) / 書式 (form) / 手続き (procedure) / BPMN (process model). It is the READ-SIDE SSoT that danjo (watches the state), kanae (fiscal-flow viz), tsumugi (power-graph), toritsugi (citizen procedure concierge) and himotoki (disclosure) all consume for the 'who / where / how' of public administration — so they stop re-deriving it ad hoc. CONSTITUTIONAL POSTURE: an OBSERVATIONAL MIRROR + civic wayfinding map, exactly like tsumugi ('accountability map, NEVER a target-list') and watatsuna ('resilience map, NEVER a target-list'). Per-unit atlas DIDs (did:web:etzhayyim.com:gov:<iso3>:...) identify ooyake's MIRROR RECORD of a real public body — they NEVER claim to BE the government, NEVER are an official channel, NEVER issue/accept anything on a government's behalf (§2(c) impersonation ban, G3). ooyake is READ-ONLY: it catalogs; it never files/submits/mutates a government record (→ toritsugi, gated) and never audits/adjudicates (→ danjo). Public-data-only (G4), non-fabrication with provenance + last-verified + :authoritative/:representative sourcing (G5), no personal data of officials (G6), Murakumo-only (G7), non-commercial (G8), read-side-only (G9), civic-wayfinding-never-target-list (G10), politically neutral (G11), freshness-gated (G12). JP-first proof-of-model (R0); architecture jurisdiction-generic. Amends ADR-2605242330 §2 (per-unit enumeration admitted as a bounded read-side atlas, NOT routing-around). 7 cells / 8 Lexicons / 12 gates / 11 non-goals.",
  "descriptionJa": "全世界の政府単位を網羅する kotoba-Datomic-native の構造アトラス — 超国家 → 国 → 広域/地方 → 都道府県 → 市区町村 → 省 → 庁 → 局 → 課 → 係 → 窓口 まで。各単位が 住所 / 窓口 / 書式 / 手続き / BPMN を保持する。danjo(国家を監視)・kanae(財政フロー可視化)・tsumugi(権力グラフ)・toritsugi(市民手続きコンシェルジュ)・himotoki(開示)が公共行政の『誰が/どこで/どうやって』を引くための READ-SIDE な SSoT(各 actor が個別に再構築しなくて済む)。憲法的姿勢: tsumugi(『説明責任マップであって標的リストではない』)・watatsuna(『レジリエンス・マップであって標的リストではない』)と同じく、観察ミラー + 市民導線マップ。単位ごとの atlas DID(did:web:etzhayyim.com:gov:<iso3>:...)は実在の公的機関に対する ooyake のミラー記録を指すのであって、政府そのものを名乗らない・公式 channel ではない・政府の代わりに何かを発行/受理しない(§2(c) なりすまし禁止、G3)。ooyake は READ-ONLY: カタログ化のみ。政府記録の提出/変更は行わない(→ toritsugi、gated)。監査/裁定もしない(→ danjo)。公開データのみ(G4)、provenance + last-verified + :authoritative/:representative sourcing による非捏造(G5)、職員個人情報の不保持(G6)、Murakumo-only(G7)、非営利(G8)、read-side のみ(G9)、市民導線であって標的リストにしない(G10)、政治的中立(G11)、freshness-gated(G12)。日本先行の proof-of-model(R0);architecture は jurisdiction 汎用。ADR-2605242330 §2 を改正(単位列挙を『routing-around ではなく read-side アトラス』として限定的に許容)。7 cells / 8 Lexicons / 12 gates / 11 non-goals。",
  "adr": {
    "master": "etzhayyim:adr:2606021600",
    "parent": "etzhayyim:adr:2605212100",
    "r0": "etzhayyim:adr:2606021600",
